Broadway, north from West 184th Street, showing an old house at 186th Street and St. Elizabeths Church (R. C.) at 187th Street. On the ridge are the Sweetser, Witherspoon and Bernard places. These are seen also in view 2.

E. P. Chrystie

March 11, 1923
Views 1, 2

Broadway, north from West 184th Street, showing an old house at 186th Street and St. Elizabeths Church (R. C.) at 187th Street. On the ridge are the Sweetser, Witherspoon and Bernard places. These are seen also in view 2.

E. P. Chrystie

March 11, 1923
Views 1, 2

(1)

4320-4324 Broadway, at and adjoining the N.E. corner of 184th Street. The two centre buildings are three-story frame houses.

1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection Museum of the City of New York. Negative No. 65.

(2)

The same view from a slightly different angle. Note frame house at the rear of No. 4322, adjoining the N.E. corner.
November 3, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)

Another view of the afore mentioned corner, and also including a further view northward.
November 3, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
